# PLACEHOLDER — STRUCTURE NOT ENCODABLE AS NAMED.
#
# Citreoviridin (PubChem CID 6436023, ChemSpider 4940705,
# C23H30O6, MW 402.48) is NOT macrocyclic. It cannot be the
# product of a macrocyclization rule, transannular Diels-Alder
# or otherwise.
#
# AWAITING IVAN'S DECISION on reassigning this slot. Candidates:
#   - Cassaine via TDA: Phoenix, S.; Reddy, M. S.; Deslongchamps, P.
#     J. Am. Chem. Soc. 2008, 130, 13989-13995.
#     DOI: 10.1021/ja805097s
#   - Berube-Deslongchamps 1987 13-membered macrocyclic triene
#     (methodology paper, not a total synthesis):
#     Tetrahedron Lett. 1987, 28, 5249-5252.
#     DOI: 10.1016/S0040-4039(00)96699-1
#
# If the slot is reassigned to citreoviridin under a DIFFERENT
# rule (Option A in research_brief.md §4), the SMILES for the
# natural product is:
#   COc1cc(=O)oc(/C=C/C=C/C=C/C(C)=C/[C@]2(C)O[C@H](C)[C@@](C)(O)[C@H]2O)c1C
# but no `transannular_diels_alder` rule fires on this molecule.
#
# Do not autopopulate this file. See notes.md.
